The above considerations can form four cases for 2D bilayer materials with interlayer sliding, and we can analyze their symmetries with an abstract bilayer crystal model which only considers the above crystal symmetries and ignores the specific crystal structures. The complete symmetry analysis for each case is summarized in Supplementary Note 1, and the corresponding results are shown in Table 1. As can be seen, Case 1b and Case 2a host the out-of-plane polarization, and the two opposite interlayer-sliding states are correlated by M̂xy\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
