We can calculate the light-induced out-of-plane electric dipole moment and voltage caused by the out-of-plane BPVE, and estimate the possibility to flip the ferroelectric order. With light power of 2.65 × 1011 W/cm2 (equivalent electric field E=1 V/nm) and a typical value of σxx′z=σyy′z\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
